# Joseph as chief administrator of Egypt — national famine-management plan.
# Phase artifact: closure-stabilization (domain fragment). the famine response stabilizes Egypt and the program closes.
# One admitted PDDL Turtle planning artifact; fragments across all phase
# artifacts merge structurally into ONE combined plan (domain name
# 'joseph-famine' shared by every fragment). Formal planning-to-workflow
# demonstration domain; argues no doctrine, claims no historicity.
@prefix ex: <http://example.org/joseph#> .
@prefix ceng: <urn:chatman:engine#> .

ex:egypt ex:preserved ex:through-famine .

ex:closure-stabilization ceng:pddlDomain """
(define (domain joseph-famine)
  (:requirements :strips)
  (:predicates
    (land-livestock-transferred ?x)
    (famine-stabilized ?x)
    (program-closed ?x))
  (:action stabilize-famine-response
    :parameters (?x)
    :precondition (and (land-livestock-transferred ?x))
    :effect (and (famine-stabilized ?x)))
  (:action close-program
    :parameters (?x)
    :precondition (and (famine-stabilized ?x))
    :effect (and (program-closed ?x))))
""" .
